Walsh-Hadamard Spectral Analysis of h[0] at N=4
200K samples per mask, 32 weight-1 + 500 weight-2 + 2000 random masks

Weight-1: best bias 0.0022 (= random baseline)
Weight-2: best bias 0.0039 at bits (14,17)
Random (weight 1-16): best bias 0.0038 (mask 0x10019020, hw=5)

CONCLUSION: No significant linear bias. h[0] is well-balanced.
Linear cryptanalysis on individual bits is not viable.
